Column.name: Note
Column.value: A formal agreement that specifies the terms and conditions of the relationship between an employee and an employer including compensation and expectations. (Business Dictionary)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Specifies a series of stages that characterize the course of existence of an employee relationship including five stages: Recruitment, Onboarding, Development, Retention, and Exit/Separation/Offboarding.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A specific party who plays a specific role in a specific employee relationship.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A relationship between an employer and its employee focused on enabling employee to collaborate on typical managerial tasks with its employer.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: This stage includes all the processes in which employees are given feedback for their work through performance reviews, one-on-one check-ins and meetings.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: At this stage, employees who have accepted job offers become part of the company's workforce. (giving a new hire the information and tools needed to start working).

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A specific role of a specific Party in the specific relationship.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: This stage is about retaining the worker and ensuring continued employee development. Continuous evaluation, recognition and training are crucial at this stage for sustaining employee engagement and retaining the employee.

Column.value:
A relationship between two or more parties; the parties involved are specified in terms of the roles they play in the relationship.
A Party Relationship is a connection between an instance of a Party and two or more instances of associated objects in the relationship.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: This is the final stage of the employee life cycle, wherein the employee leaves due to a new job, retirement, layoffs, personal reasons or termination for violating company policy.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Specifies a series of stages that characterize the course of existence of a party relationship in a specific context.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: This stage includes all the processes leading up to and including the hiring of a new employee.
